{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Isa|14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","chapter":14,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":1,"text":"For the Lord will have compassion on Jacob and will choose Israel again. He will settle them on their own land. The resident alien will join them and be united with the house of Jacob.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":2,"text":"The nations will escort Israel and bring it to its homeland. Then the house of Israel will possess them as male and female slaves in the Lord’s land. They will make captives of their captors and will rule over their oppressors.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":3,"text":"When the Lord gives you rest from your pain, torment, and the hard labor you were forced to do,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":4,"text":"you will sing this song of contempt about the king of Babylon and say:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":5,"text":"The Lord has broken the staff of the wicked,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":6,"text":"It struck the peoples in anger","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:14:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":14,"verse":